I"à<p>In 2019, a team of New Zealand zoologists, searching for a common insect, made an incredible discovery.</p>

<p>Professor Jon Waters &amp; PhD student Brodi Foster from the University of Otago ventured into the Maungatua Range near Dunedin in search of a widespread species of stonefly when he stumbled upon a new species. This species of wingless stonefly has been sitting undiscovered in the mountains for 2 million years.</p>

<p>This short film outlines the discovery.</p>
